The paper focuses on audio visual scene-aware dialogue (AVSD), which involves connecting audio, vision, and language. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) sub-categories of computer science. Therefore, cs.CL and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a mechanism that fuses features and attention in multiple stages, which involves machine learning techniques. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (AI), machine learning (LG), and multimedia (MM) sub-categories.
